The launch will take place from Cape Canaveral Space Force Station, Florida, during a window beginning at 3 p.m. EDT (1900 GMT). This will be Amazon's first major batch of satellites for Project Kuiper, comprising the heaviest payload ever flown by Atlas V. The mission marks just the second ever Project Kuiper launch and the first with Amazon's finalized satellite design.

The rocket's first stage landed successfully on the drone ship 'Just Read the Instructions' in the Atlantic Ocean. This mission marked the 17th flight for this booster, previously used for 10 Starlink launches. The Starlink satellites were deployed to low Earth orbit, further expanding SpaceX's global internet constellation.

launchData.location: Europe's Spaceport, Kourou, French Guiana
launchData.description: Vega-C will launch the European Space Agency's Biomass forest-monitoring satellite to sun-synchronous orbit.
launchData.article_summary: The European Space Agency (ESA) is set to launch its Biomass forest-monitoring satellite aboard a Vega-C rocket from Europe's Spaceport in Kourou, French Guiana, on April 29, 2025, at 09:15 UTC. The mission will deploy the 1,130-kilogram Biomass spacecraft into a sun-synchronous orbit 666 kilometers above Earth. Biomass will use synthetic aperture radar (SAR) to study global forests, mapping their structure and monitoring carbon storage over its planned five-year mission. This is the fourth flight of Vega-C, operated by Arianespace, and the second since the vehicle's return to flight after a 2022 anomaly.

launchData.description: Atlas V launches 27 Amazon Project Kuiper broadband satellites into low Earth orbit.
launchData.article_summary: United Launch Alliance's Atlas V rocket launched the first major batch of 27 Amazon Project Kuiper broadband satellites from Cape Canaveral Space Force Station on April 28, 2025, at 23:01 UTC. This marks the start of Amazon's plan to build a massive constellation of over 3,200 satellites to provide global internet coverage, in competition with SpaceX's Starlink network. The satellites will be raised to their operational orbits after initial deployment. The launch experienced previous weather-related delays but ultimately proceeded successfully. Most of the future Kuiper launches will also use ULA's Atlas V and Vulcan Centaur, with some contracts awarded to Blue Origin, SpaceX, and Arianespace.

launchData.article_summary: On April 28, 2025, a brand-new SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket successfully launched 23 Starlink broadband satellites, 13 of which feature direct-to-cell capability, from Kennedy Space Center in Florida at 10:34 p.m. EDT (2:34 UTC April 29). This mission marked the Falcon 9 booster’s first flight, which subsequently landed on the 'A Shortfall of Gravitas' droneship in the Atlantic Ocean. The upper stage will deploy the satellites to low Earth orbit, further expanding SpaceX's Starlink constellation. This flight was SpaceX's 50th Falcon 9 launch of 2025, with 33 dedicated to Starlink.

launchData.article_summary: The US Army launched its Long-Range Hypersonic Weapon, officially named 'Dark Eagle,' from Cape Canaveral Space Force Station. The early morning test flight aims to validate the missile for possible deployment later in 2025. Designed for rapid, conventional strikes, this marks the first ground-based hypersonic missile launch from Cape Canaveral since 1988. The test follows a previous successful flight, signaling significant progress for US hypersonic capabilities.
